            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Use `$NVIM_LISTEN_ADDRESS` environment variable and a shell hook like\n\n``` Python\n#!/usr/bin/env python\n# neovim-autocd.py\nimport neovim\nimport os\n\nnvim = neovim.attach('socket', os.environ['NVIM_LISTEN_ADDRESS'])\nnvim.vars['__autocd_cwd'] = os.getcwd()\nnvim.command('execute \"lcd\" fnameescape(g:__autocd_cwd)')\ndel nvim.vars['__autocd_cwd']\n```\n\n``` Shell\n# .zshrc\nneovim_autocd() {\n    [[ $NVIM_LISTEN_ADDRESS ]] && neovim-autocd.py\n}\nchpwd_functions+=( neovim_autocd )\n```\n\nIn bash AFAIK you need to save old PWD, and use PROMPT_COMMAND to run neovim-autocd.py when it appears that $PWD â‰  saved PWD.\n\nIn any case this is not a NeoVim issue. Write a plugin if needed.\n\n(Note: with my code you need python, neovim PyPI package, but no code in VimL at all.)\n",
